er, principally due to the heavy use of the coastline and the con{\textbackslash}poundsicts between di¡erent users. From the 228 km2 of available area for sitingcages inthe coast- al regions with depth less than 50m, the total area suitable for siting cages (scores 6{\textasciicircum}8) was 37 km2. There are only 0.51km2 of very suitable areas (score 8) and approximately 5.37 km2 of suitable (score 7), most of these being located in the southeast of the is- land.These relatively small areas of suitability should be put into the context of thewider use of the coastal environment aroundTenerife.},
