al zone. As fish production increased, the location of the assemblage characteristic of the cautionary zone shifted to more open, deeper areas (lower ED values). An azoic-site group was composed of large-scale farms in a stagnant basin. The community type of the macrobenthos in the vicinity of open-water, net-pen fish farms is an indicator of the condition and assimilative capacity of the benthic environment in that area and can be used to evaluate the suitability of the site for continued fish farming. The index of embayment degree, ED, can be used as a simple and effective substitute indicator for this evaluation.},
